{
  "text": "The TGF was prepared by ''cold method\" [CITATION_1] . The poloxamer 407 solution was prepared at 4°C and it was left to stand overnight for the loss of foam formation. ON was dissolved in a mixture of ethanol and polyethylene glycol 400 (Sigma-Aldrich Co, St Louis, MO, USA) and added to the poloxamer 407 solution slowly and by being stirred at 4°C. A sufficient amount of distilled water was used in preparation of the solution. The details of all components of formulation are shown in Table 1. In the process of mixing the solutions, ice battery was used to keep the ambient temperature at 4°C. The mixture was allowed to stand at 4°C overnight to begin in vitro assays.",
